########################################################################
# Title: <type>[optional scope]: <short description>
# - Use a conventional commits type prefix (see reference below).
# - Use lowercase for type and description.
# - Do not end with a period.
# - Limit to 72 characters (the width of the line below).
########################################################################


########################################################################
# Body: Why is this change happening? (optional)
# - Describe the motivation, context, or user story.
# - Leave a blank line above to separate from the title.
# - Wrap lines at 72 characters (the width of the line below).
########################################################################


########################################################################
# Trailers: What references are relevant? (optional)
# - Must be the last part of the commit message.
# - Leave a blank line above to separate from the body.
# - Do not leave blank lines between trailers.
# - Add "BREAKING CHANGE: <description>" for breaking changes.
#
# Examples:
#
# Closes: #123
# See: https://example.com/long-url-that-does-not-need-to-be-wrapped
# Co-authored-by: Name <name@example.com>
# BREAKING CHANGE: removed support for X
#
########################################################################


########################################################################
# Reference: Conventional Commits types
# feat     = A new feature
# fix      = A bug fix
# docs     = Documentation-only changes
# style    = Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
# refactor = Code restructure without feature or fix
# perf     = Performance improvement
# test     = Add or update tests
# build    = Build system or dependency changes
# ci       = CI configuration changes
# chore    = Other changes (tooling, configs, etc.)
# revert   = Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope example: feat(fish): add mcd function
#
# Full guide: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
########################################################################
